  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 4</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 3</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 17 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 6 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 16</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> M, F, Mas</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>The most basic technique of Wato style, Shuugeki Tou Sei is a simple strike with blade kicked up to increase power. The user makes a single melee attack, that if hits deals an additional 1d4 damage per 2 levels of the user (maximum 5d4, not multiplied on critical hit).</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Mastery:</b> With the third step of mastery in this technique the user can use it as a part of a charge, but doing so increases Perform DC by 5, and Chakra Cost by 1. If the technique is used this way, the user cannot convert the cost to hit points.<br><br>Material Focus -The user's watou, katana, double katana or hansori.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
